Denmark[a] is a Nordic country in Northern Europe. It is the metropole
and most populous constituent of the Kingdom of Denmark,[N 7] also known
as the Danish Realm, a constitutionally unitary state that includes the
autonomous territories of the Faroe Islands and Greenland in the north
Atlantic Ocean.[11] Metropolitan Denmark,[N 8] also called "continental
Denmark" or "Denmark proper",[12] consists of the northern Jutland peninsula
 nd an archipelago of 406 islands.